name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client-am.ipc.max-retries
description:
The number of client retries to the AM - before reconnecting
    to the RM to fetch Application Status.
    In other words, it is the ipc.client.connect.max.retries to be used during
    reconnecting to the RM and fetching Application Status.

name: dfs.datanode.network.counts.cache.max.size
description:
The maximum number of entries the datanode per-host network error
    count cache may contain.

name: ipc.[port_number].weighted-cost.lockshared
description:
The weight multiplier to apply to the time spent in the
    processing phase which holds a shared (read) lock.
    This property applies to WeightedTimeCostProvider.

name: mapreduce.job.max.split.locations
description:
The max number of block locations to store for each split for
    locality calculation.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.suspectnode.threads
description: The maximum number of threads to use for probing suspect node.

name: dfs.edit.log.transfer.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Maximum bandwidth used for transferring edit log to between journal nodes
    for syncing, in bytes per second.
    A default value of 0 indicates that throttling is disabled.

name: dfs.mover.retry.max.attempts
description:
The maximum number of retries before the mover consider the
    move failed.

name: mapreduce.job.maps
description:
The default number of map tasks per job.
  Ignored when mapreduce.framework.name is "local".

name: dfs.block.misreplication.processing.limit
description: Maximum number of blocks to process for initializing replication queues.
